%description:
TCP AccECN (Workstream G) G7.1: AccECN TCP option read side, CEB-refined
ACE delta resolution. Deliberately constructs the scenario where G5.1's
packet-count-only safeDelta heuristic is WRONG and the AccECN option's
byte-exact CEB evidence corrects it -- the complementary case to
tcp_accecn_ace_read_1.test, which only exercised the case where safeDelta
happens to already be right.

Same base topology as tcp_accecn_ace_read_1.test (client sends 9000B/9
MSS-sized segments in one burst, server's first 8 ACKs are dropped so
only the 9th/cumulative one survives, deliveredPktsThisAck=9 so the
G5.1 packet-count-only resolution enters its "ambiguous, >7 delivered"
branch) but only the FIRST data segment (a3) is CE-marked, not all 9.
So the true CE-packet count is 1, not 9:
  - naiveDelta = (receivedAce - 5 - deliveredCePkts_before) & 7 = 1
    -- already exactly correct, no wraparound actually occurred.
  - G5.1's safeDelta, which always reinterprets the mod-8 value once
    deliveredPktsThisAck > 7 (regardless of what the true count actually
    is), computes 9 - ((9-1)&7) = 9 -- WRONG here, since only 1 of the 9
    delivered segments was actually CE-marked.
Both endpoints also have accEcnOptionEnabled=true, accEcnOptionBeaconAcks=1
(server beacons on every ACK-bearing segment), so the surviving 9th ACK
also carries a real AccECN option whose CEB field reports ~1 segment's
worth of CE bytes (corroborating naiveDelta, not safeDelta). resolveAceDelta()
compares both candidates' byte estimates (naiveDelta*mss vs safeDelta*mss)
against the observed CEB delta and correctly picks naiveDelta=1 --
deliveredCePkts lands on 1, not G5.1's uncorrected 9.

Falsification: an identical scenario with accEcnOptionEnabled=false (not
committed as a second file -- verified empirically during development,
see commit message) reproduces tcp_accecn_ace_read_1.test's own pattern:
cebDeltaValid=0, resolvedDelta falls back to the uncorrected (and here,
wrong) safeDelta=9.

%inifile: omnetpp.ini
[General]
record-vector-results = false
ned-path = .;../../../../src;../../lib

network = inet.test.moduletest.lib.TcpTestNet1

cmdenv-event-banners=false
cmdenv-express-mode=false
cmdenv-log-prefix="[%c]: "

*.testing=false
*.tcptester.script="a3 ce;b2 delete;b3 delete;b4 delete;b5 delete;b6 delete;b7 delete;b8 delete;b9 delete"

*.cli_app.localAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.cli_app.localPort=1000
*.cli_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.cli_app.connectPort=2000
*.cli_app.active=true
*.cli_app.tOpen=0s
*.cli_app.tSend=0.5s
*.cli_app.sendBytes=9000B
*.cli_app.tClose=-1s
*.cli_app.sendScript=""

*.srv_app.localAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.srv_app.localPort=2000
*.srv_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.srv_app.connectPort=1000
*.srv_app.active=false
*.srv_app.tOpen=0s
*.srv_app.tSend=-1s
*.srv_app.sendBytes=0B
*.srv_app.tClose=-1s
*.srv_app.sendScript=""

*.*_tcp.sackSupport = false
*.*_tcp.windowScalingSupport = false
*.*_tcp.timestampSupport = false
*.*_tcp.mss = 1000
*.*_tcp.tcpAlgorithmClass = "TcpReno"
*.*_tcp.delayedAcksEnabled = false
*.*_tcp.initialWindow = "rfc6928"

*.*_tcp.tcpEcnMode = "accecn"
*.*_tcp.accEcnOptionEnabled = true
*.*_tcp.accEcnOptionBeaconAcks = 1

# tcp-legacy.ini sets advertisedWindow=7504; OMNeT++ ini resolution takes the FIRST matching
# entry, so this override -- needed so the full 9000B burst fits in one window and all 9
# segments go out without waiting on an intermediate ACK -- must appear BEFORE the include.
*.*_tcp.advertisedWindow = 20000

include ../../lib/tcp-legacy.ini

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: postrun.pl
open FILE, '<test.out';
while($sor = <FILE>)
{
    if ($sor =~ /^\[testing\]: (.*)$/)
    {
        print "$1\n";
    }
}
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command:  perl ./postrun.pl
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Server's surviving (9th real) ACK: ace=6=0b110, covering the 9-segment burst (option overhead
%# reduces per-segment payload below 1000B, so 9000B took 10 segments in total -- one extra small
%# segment, A012/B011, follows this one and is unrelated to the assertion below). CEB=988 reflects
%# exactly the one CE-marked segment's (a3's) real payload length.
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[0.503 B010] A.1000 < B.2000: A W N ack 8893 win 20000   Option(s): NOP AccECN(kind=172,E0B=1,E1B=1,CEB=988)
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# The G7.1 assertion: CEB evidence (cebDelta=988, matching naiveDelta*mss exactly) correctly
%# overrides G5.1's uncorrected, wrong-in-this-scenario safeDelta=9 back to naiveDelta=1.
%contains: stdout
AccECN ACE decode: receivedAce=6 deliveredPktsThisAck=9 naiveDelta=1 safeDelta=9 cebDeltaValid=1 cebDelta=988 resolvedDelta=1 deliveredCePkts=1
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
